<p class=MsoNormal align=right dir=RTL style='text-align:left'><span dir=LTR></span><span
dir=LTR><span dir=LTR></span>38. <span style='mso-spacerun:yes'> </span>The
third (lice), sixth (<span class=SpellE>shchin</span> - boils), <span
class=GramE>ninth(</span>darkness) and the first born.<span
style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>It seems that the principle of <span
class=SpellE>hazaka</span> is in play here since always the third plague is
without warning.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span><span class=GramE>And
then the third of the three.</span> </span><span lang=HE><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=right dir=RTL style='text-align:left'><span dir=LTR></span><span
dir=LTR><span dir=LTR></span>39. It is forbidden by Jewish custom to eat <span
class=SpellE>matzah</span> from 30 days before <span class=GramE>Pesach ,</span>
i.e. Purim.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=right dir=RTL style='text-align:left'><span dir=LTR>40.
It is forbidden to eat <span class=SpellE>hametz</span> according to Torah law
from </span><st1:time Minute="0" Hour="12"><span dir=LTR>noon</span></st1:time><span
dir=LTR> on Pesach eve. But <span class=SpellE>rabbinically</span> it is
forbidden two hours before that.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=right dir=RTL style='text-align:left'><span dir=LTR>41.
Because it is written in <span class=SpellE>Shmot</span> </span><st1:time
Minute="26" Hour="15"><span dir=LTR>15:26</span></st1:time><span dir=LTR>
(right after </span><st1:place><span dir=LTR>Red Sea</span></st1:place><span
dir=LTR> crossing) that all the illnesses of </span><st1:country-region><st1:place><span
  dir=LTR>Egypt</span></st1:place></st1:country-region><span dir=LTR> G-d will
save the Israelites from. So, the more illnesses there were, the more we will
be saved from!</span></p>

