<p class=MsoNormal align=right dir=RTL style='text-align:left'><span dir=LTR></span><span
dir=LTR><span dir=LTR></span>45. Rashi Brings that with a heh it means "with their wispers"
 and without a heh it means "with a wisper done secretly".  Rashi also quotes Sanhedrin 67 that
without a heh means using is Maaseh Shedim and with a heh it means
 Maaseh Kshafim.  


